# Code Principles & Best Practices

## Core Principles
- **Keep It Simple**: Avoid over-engineering
- **DRY & SOLID**: Extract common code; single responsibility
- **Readability First**: Self-documenting code; clear names over comments

## Anti-Patterns
- Unnecessary abstraction layers or "manager" classes
- Deep inheritance; premature optimization

## Preferred Patterns
- Composition over inheritance
- Small focused functions (aim ~20–30 lines)
- Immutable data where possible
- Fail fast with meaningful errors
